      PROGRAM sph
!************************************************************
!************************************************************
!************************************************************
!******************                    **********************
!******************    S    P    H     **********************
!******************                    **********************
!************************************************************
!************************************************************
!************************************************************
!                                                           *
!  This is a three-dimensional hydro code based on the      *
!  so-called smoothed particles hydrodynamics method.       *
!                                                           *
!************************************************************
!                                                           *
!  W. Benz        Los Alamos National Laboratory 31/08/86   *
!                 Harvard College Observatory    10/03/87   *
!                                                           *
!  I. A. Bonnell  University de Montreal         XX/XX/91   *
!                 University of Cambridge, UK    01/10/92   *
!                                                           *
!  M. R. Bate     University of Cambridge, UK    01/10/92   *
!                                                           *
!************************************************************
!                                                           *
!  Modifications by: I. A. Bonnell      UdeM    28/05/92    *
!                                                           *
!  (1) random number generator from Numerical Recipes: ran1 *
!  (2) cylindrical boundaries (ibound = 2): ghosp2          *
!  (3) gforsa and gforsn are parallelized                   *
!  (4) generator of axial density perturbations (ibound = 2)*
!                                                           *
!  Major Modifications by: M. R. Bate   UofCam  31/01/95    *
!                                                           *
!  (1) individual particle timesteps                        *
!  (2) inclusion of accreting, massive point masses (sink   *
!         particles) with boundaries, identified by iphase. *
!  (3) corrected ghost boundaries                           *
!  (4) constant pressure boundaries                         *
!                                                           *
!  Major Modifications by: M. R. Bate and R. Klessen        *
!                                         MPIA  02/02/96    *
!                                                           *
!  (1) switchable between BINARY TREE and GRAPE board       *
!         computation of gravity and neighbours lists       *
!                                                           *
!************************************************************
!  General Description                                      *
!                                                           *
!  This code allows three different type of tasks to be     *
!  done according to variable "job" . Variable job is read  *
!  from the command line.                                   *
!                                                           *
!  1) job=initial                                           *
!     -----------                                           *
!     this allows to compute new initial conditions. This   *
!     can be done by either starting from scratch or by     *
!     adding two existing situations together               *
!     (see subroutine newrun)                               *
!                                                           *
!  2) job=transfer                                          *
!     -------------                                         *
!     this allows to copy one or several dumps from one     *
!     file to another one. During this transfer  there is   *
!     a possibility of making changes in the various        *
!     quantities                                            *
!     (see subroutine transfd)                              *
!                                                           *
!  3) job=evolution                                         *
!     -------------                                         *
!     this allows to compute the actual evolution of the    *
!     system by specifying the various forces to be         *
!     included                                              *
!     (see subroutine evol)                                 *
!                                                           *
!************************************************************
!                                                           *
!  Running SPH                                              *
!  ===========                                              *
!                                                           *
!  The main option of the code, JOB, is read from the       *
!  command line. If JOB=INITIAL or TRANSFER, the code goes  *
!  into an interactive mode. Just answer the questions      *
!  after having read the informations below. If EVOLUTION   *
!  is chosen, the code is looking for a file called INSPH   *
!  where the various options have to be defined.            *
!                                                           *
!  files used and written by the code:                      *
!  -----------------------------------                      *
!                                                           *
!  1) If JOB=INITIAL and the SCRATCH option is chosen, then *
!     the code does not need any files but will produce     *
!     a binary file containing all the quantities needed    *
!     for the evolution part. Furthemore, the code produces *
!     an ascii file callled OUTSPH summarizing the code's   *
!     actions.                                              *
!  2) If JOB=INITIAL and the EXIST option is chosen, then   *
!     the code will require two files containing data to    *
!     combine them into a third file. An ascii file OUTSPH  *
!     is also produced.                                     *
!  3) If JOB=TRANSFER the code needs an existing binary file*
!     and upon completion it will create another one. Again *
!     an ascii file OUTSPH is created                       *
!  4) If JOB=EVOLUTION the code needs a binary file with    *
!     initial conditions produces by the INITIAL evolution  *
!     or the file resulting from a prior evolution run.     *
!     Again the file OUTSPH is produced and contains all    *
!     informations regarding the status of the evolution.   *
!     It is important to check the file periodically and    *
!     monitor the total energy and angular momentum for     *
!     example since both should be conserved (within 2% say)*
!                                                           *
!  Various important details                                *
!  -------------------------                                *
!  1) The code checks the size of the binary file. If it    *
!     grows beyond 10Mb it opens a new one. To keep track   *
!     of all these files, the code assumes that the name of *
!     the binary file is of the form XXXXXYY. XXXXX being   *
!     characters and YY numbers (typically 01 at the start).*
!     When a new file is created, its name will be XXXXXYY+1*
!     (see subroutine FILE)                                 *
!  2) The number of neighbors for each particles is  stored *
!     using the parameter ILIST. If dimensions too small    *
!     the code will issue a warning message but do the job. *
!     The dimensions should however be changed.             *
!  3) The code checks periodically for a file called        *
!     MESSAGE. This file permits to change some of the      *
!     options defined in the input deck during the code's   *
!     execution (see MESOP)                                 *
!  4) The debug option IDEBUG should be used with care since*
!     it produces a lont of output! ITRACE can be set to all*
!     to trace the code through the various subroutines in  *
!     case of misterious errors!                            *
!  5) All forces can be turned off or on at will except for *
!     pressure gradients than should always be on.          *
!  6) The code in its present version assumes a perfect gas *
!     equation of state (see EOSPG). This can be complicated*
!     at will!.                                             *
!  7) The number of particles that can be used is determined*
!     by the parameter IDIM. The number of particles NPART  *
!     has to be less (or equal) to IDIM.                    *
!  8) Before anything can be done with the code, the proper *
!     units have to be defined (see UNIT). The number to    *
!     input are the total mass and a length scale. These    *
!     numbers are actually inside the code and not options  *
!     since for any particular choice of units, they should *
!     not be changed anymore! Once both numbers have been   *
!     coded in, the code determines all other units.        *
!  9) The sum of the mass of all particles should be equal 1*
!     unless, the total mass given in UNIT is not the one   *
!     represented by the particles.                         *
!                                                           *
!                                                           *
!-----------------------------------------------------------*
!                                                           *
!  job=evolution input deck (see OPTIONS)                   *
!  --------------------------------------                   *
!                                                           *
!  namerun  = name of the run                               *
!  file1    = name of file containing starting dump and on  *
!             which new dumps are added                     *
!  varsta   = entropy : use entropy as variable of state    *
!           = intener : use specific internal energy as     *
!                       variable of state                   *
!                                                           *
!  --------------                                           *
!  igrp     = 0       : no pressure gradients               *
!             1       : with pressure gradients             *
!  igphi    = 0       : no self-gravity                     *
!             1       : with self-gravity                   *
!  ifsvi    = 0       : no artificial viscosity             *
!             1       : with artificial viscosity           *
!  ifcor    = 0       : no coriolis forces                  *
!             1       : with coriolis forces                *
!  ichoc    = 0       : no heating due to artif. viscosity  *
!             1       : with heating due to artif. viscosity*
!  iener    = 0       : no total energy conservation        *
!             1       : with total energy conservation      *
!  damp     = value of general damping coefficient          *
!  ibound   = 0       : no boundaries                       *
!             1       : with reflective boundaries          *
!  iexf     = 0       : no external forces                  *
!          >= 1       : allow for external forces           *
!  iexpan   = 0       : no general expansion                *
!             1       : general expansion superposed        *
!                                                           *
!  the external force, the boundaries and the general       *
!  damping are NOT considered in the energy equation.       *
!                                                           *
!  --------------                                           *
!  nstep    = frequency at which timesteps are written on   *
!             disk                                          *
!  tdump    = time between dumps (alternative to number     *
!             of steps between dumps)                       *
!  tnext    = time of next dump                             *
!  tol      = tolerance used by the Runge-Kutta integrator  *
!  ipos     = 9999    : use last dump as starting dump      *
!           = number  : use number as starting dump (all    *
!                       dumps behond number are destroyed!) *
!  tmax     = max time in minute allowed for the job        *
!  tstop    = time (computer unit) at which the program     *
!             will stop.                                    *
!                                                           *
!  only if iexpan= 1                                        *
!  -----------------                                        *
!  vexpan    =  expansion velocity of the frame of ref. in  *
!               cm/s.                                       *
!                                                           *
!  only if ifcor=1                                          *
!  ---------------                                          *
!  omeg0     =  angular velocity of the reference frame in  *
!               1/s                                         *
!                                                           *
!  only if ibound=1                                         *
!  ----------------                                         *
!  (all boundaries are used, if only one type is desired    *
!   it is necessary to set the other far away ... )         *
!                                                           *
!  rmax      =  max. radius for spherical boundary          *
!  xmin,xmax =  min and max x coord. for boundary           *
!  ymin,ymax =  min and max y coord. for boundary           *
!  zmin,zmax =  min and max z coord. for boundary           *
!                                                           *
!                                                           *
!************************************************************
!                                                           *
!  alphabetical list of common variables                    *
!  =====================================                    *
!                                                           *
!  variable  common block   description                     *
!- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -*
!                                                           *
!  alpha        (shock) : coefficient for bulk viscosity    *
!  angto        (angm ) : total angular momentum            *
!  angx         (angm ) : x componant of total angular mom. *
!  angy         (angm ) : y componant of total angular mom. *
!  angz         (angm ) : z componant of total angular mom. *
!  artvix(idim) (artv1) : x componant of artif. viscosity   *
!                         pressure gradient                 *
!  artviy(idim) (artv1) : y componant of artif. viscosity   *
!                         pressure gradient                 *
!  artviz(idim) (artv1) : z componant of artif. viscosity   *
!                         pressure gradient                 *
!  beta         (shock) : coefficient for Neumann-Richtmeyer*
!                         viscosity                         *
!  cmx1         (out1 ) : x coord. of c.m. body 1           *
!  cmy1         (out1 ) : y coord. of c.m. body 1           *
!  cmz1         (out1 ) : z coord. of c.m. body 1           *
!  cmx2         (out2 ) : x coord. of c.m. body 2           *
!  cmy2         (out2 ) : y coord. of c.m. body 2           *
!  cmz2         (out2 ) : z coord. of c.m. body 2           *
!  cnormk       (kerne) : normalisation constant of kernel  *
!  damp         (dissi) : general damping coefficient       *
!  dq(idim)     (ener1) : heating due to shock dissipation  *
!  dt           (time ) : current timestep                  *
!  dvtable      (table) : spacing between table values      *
!  encal        (cgas ) : eos/energy calculation method flag*
!  escap        (fracg) : mass of escapors                  *
!  file1        (file ) : name of file number 1             *
!  file2        (file ) : name of file number 2             *
!  file3        (file ) : name of file number 3             *
!  fmass(itable)(table) : mass of particle as a funct. of r *
!  fmas1        (bodys) : fraction of total mass in body 1  *
!  fmas2        (bodys) : fraction of total mass in body 2  *
!  fnbtot       (units) : number of total mass              *
!  fpoten(itable)(table): potential energy as a funct. of r *
!  fx(idim)     (force) : x componant of total force        *
!  fy(idim)     (force) : y componant of total force        *
!  fz(idim)     (force) : z componant of total force        *
!  gamma        (cgas ) : value of gamma                    *
!  gradpx(idim) (gradp) : x componant of pressure gradients *
!  gradpy(idim) (gradp) : y componant of pressure gradients *
!  gradpz(idim) (gradp) : z componant of pressure gradients *
!  gravx(idim)  (gravi) : x componant of body forces        *
!  gravy(idim)  (gravi) : y componant of body forces        *
!  gravz(idim)  (gravi) : z componant of body forces        *
!  grwij(itable)(table) : gradient of kernel table          *
!  gt           (gtime) : current global time in code units *
!  h(idim)      (kerne) : smoothing length                  *
!  hma1         (out1 ) : max h for body 1                  *
!  hma2         (out2 ) : max h for body 2                  *
!  hmi1         (out1 ) : min h for body 1                  *
!  hmi2         (out2 ) : min h for body 2                  *
!  ibound       (typef) : flag to allow boundaries          *
!  icell(i,j,k) (nlist) : chaining mesh cells               *
!  ichoc        (typef) : flag to allow shock heating       *
!  idebug       (debug) : debug option                      *
!  idisk1       (logun) : logical unit number for disk file *
!  idisk2       (logun) : logical unit number for disk file *
!  idisk3       (logun) : logical unit number for disk file *
!  idist        (new  ) : type of distribution for setting  *
!                         the initial particles             *
!  idumy        (random): number to initialize generator    *
!  iener        (typef) : flag to allow total energy cons.  *
!  iexf         (typef) : flag to allow external forces     *
!  iexpan       (typef) : flag to allow expansion           *
!  ifcor        (typef) : flag to allow coriolis forces     *
!  ifsvi        (typef) : flag to allow arti. viscosity     *
!  igrp         (typef) : flag to allow pressure gradients  *
!  igphi        (typef) : flag to allow body forces         *
!  ipos         (recor) : record number wanted on disk      *
!  iprint       (logun) : logical unit number for print out *
!  irec         (recor) : record number on disk             *
!  iterm        (logun) : logical unit number for read      *
!  itrace       (debug) : flag to allow flow tracing        *
!  job          (actio) : main option that tells the code   *
!                         what option it has to run         *
!  n1           (bodys) : number of particles in body 1     *
!  n2           (bodys) : number of particles in body 2     *
!  namerun      (actio) : name of the run                   *
!  ncount       (tming) : number of timestep since last dump*
!                         was written on disk               *
!  np           (new  ) : number of particles at initial.   *
!  npart        (part ) : total number of particles         *
!  nstep        (tming) : number of  timestep between disk  *
!                         dumps                             *
!  tdump        (tming) : time between disk dumps           *
!                         (alternative to number of steps)  *
!  tnext        (tming) : time of next dump                 *
!  omeg0        (rotat) : angular velocity of frame of ref. *
!  partm        (new  ) : particles mass                    *
!  pdv(idim)    (ener1) : pdv work on particle              *
!  pmass(idim)  (carac) : mass of particles                 *
!  poten(idim)  (ener1) : potential energy of particle      *
!  pr(idim)     (eosq ) : pressure at particle locations    *
!  qphys(idco)  (tcond) : physical thermal conductivity     *
!  rho(idim)    (densi) : density at particle locations     *
!  rmax         (rbnd ) : max radius of boundary            *
!  romax1       (out1 ) : max density in body 1             *
!  romax2       (out2 ) : max density in body 2             *
!  romean1      (out1 ) : mean density body 1               *
!  romean2      (out2 ) : mean density body 2               *
!  v0           (space) : frac. of h of init. lattice cell  *
!  tgrav        (ener2) : total gravitational energy        *
!  thermal1     (new  ) : either entropy or int. energy at  *
!                         initialisation                    *
!  thermal2     (new  ) : either entropy or int. energy at  *
!                         initialisation                    *
!  thermal3     (new  ) : either entropy or int. energy at  *
!                         initialisation                    *
!  thick        (new  ) : thickness ratio of initial plate  *
!  tkin         (ener2) : total kinetic energy              *
!  tmax         (tming) : maximum time allowed for the job  *
!  totm         (new  ) : total mass represented by part.   *
!  trot         (ener2) : total rotational energy           *
!  tstep        (tming) : cpu time needed for one timestep  *
!  tstop        (tming) : time at which simulation has to   *
!                         stop (code units)                 *
!  tterm        (ener2) : total thermal energy              *
!  u(idim)      (part ) : total specific internal energy    *
!  udens        (units) : unit of density                   *
!  udist        (units) : unit of length                    *
!  uergg        (units) : unit of energy per unit mass      *
!  uergcc       (units) : unit of pressure                  *
!  umass        (units) : unit of mass                      *
!  utime        (units) : unit of time                      *
!  varsta       (varet) : variable of state beside density  *
!  vcmx1        (out1 ) : x comp. of velocity of cm body 1  *
!  vcmy1        (out1 ) : y comp. of velocity of cm body 1  *
!  vcmz1        (out1 ) : z comp. of velocity of cm body 1  *
!  vcmx2        (out2 ) : x comp. of velocity of cm body 2  *
!  vcmy2        (out2 ) : y comp. of velocity of cm body 2  *
!  vcmz2        (out2 ) : z comp. of velocity of cm body 2  *
!  version      (infor) : version of the code               *
!  vexpan       (expan) : expansion velocity                *
!  vsmax        (eosq ) : maximum sound speed               *
!  vsound(idim) (eosq ) : sound speed at particle locations *
!  vvx1         (new  ) : x componant of velocity of center *
!                         of mass body 1                    *
!  vvx2         (new  ) : x componant of velocity of center *
!                         of mass body 2                    *
!  vvy1         (new  ) : y componant of velocity of center *
!                         of mass body 1                    *
!  vvy2         (new  ) : y componant of velocity of center *
!                         of mass body 2                    *
!  vvz1         (new  ) : z componant of velocity of center *
!                         of mass body 1                    *
!  vvz2         (new  ) : z componant of velocity of center *
!                         of mass body 2                    *
!  vx(idim)     (part ) : x componant of the part. velocity *
!  vy(idim)     (part ) : y componant of the part. velocity *
!  vz(idim)     (part ) : z componant of the part. velocity *
!  what         (new  ) : gives type of initialisation      *
!  wij(itable)  (table) : table of kernel values            *
!  x(idim)      (part ) : x coordinate of the particles     *
!  xmax         (rbnd ) : position of upper reflec. bound.  *
!  xmin         (rbnd ) : position of lower reflec. bound.  *
!  xx1          (new  ) : x coordinate of center of mass    *
!                         body 1                            *
!  xx2          (new  ) : x coordinate of center of mass    *
!                         body 2                            *
!  y(idim)      (part ) : y coordinate of the particles     *
!  ymax         (rbnd ) : position of upper reflec. bound.  *
!  ymin         (rbnd ) : position of lower reflec. bound.  *
!  yy1          (new  ) : y coordinate of center of mass    *
!                         body 1                            *
!  yy2          (new  ) : y coordinate of center of mass    *
!                         body 2                            *
!  z(idim)      (part ) : z coordinate of the particles     *
!  zmax         (rbnd ) : position of upper reflec. bound.  *
!  zmin         (rbnd ) : position of lower reflec. bound.  *
!  zz1          (new  ) : z coordinate of center of mass    *
!                         body 1                            *
!  zz2          (new  ) : z coordinate of center of mass    *
!                         body 2                            *
!                                                           *
!************************************************************
!                                                           *
!  timing and memory requirements                           *
!  ==============================                           *
!                                                           *
!  Both vary enormously with the various options chosen.    *
!  Running time scales like NlogN.                          *
!                                                           *
!************************************************************

      use mpi_mod
      use idims

      use infor
      use actio
      use debug

      implicit none

      REAL(DP) dummytime
      REAL(DP) :: ran1
!
!--Version - date is date last updated with other code version changes
!
      version = 'SPH3D-PTM-MULTI-TDISKS+WINDS-COOLING-25APR2023'

!   Same as version = 'SPH3D-PTM-DISKS+WINDS-COOLING-03MAY2010', but
!
!   Same as version = 'SPH3DT-PTMAS-DEC+ACC+CW-07MAY2008', but
!     includes the effect of optically thin radiative cooling.
!
!     version = 'SPH3DT-PTMAS-DEC+ACC+CW-07MAY2008'
!
!   Same as version ='SPH3DT-PTMAS-DEC+ACC+CW-15FEB2007', but
!     includes igeom=8 for a wind from an equatorial sector and
!     have modifications mainly to enable wind accretion simulations.
!     The way the wind parameters are given has also been changed from
!     the 15-02-2007 version.
!
!     version = 'SPH3DT-PTMAS-DEC+ACC+CW-15FEB2007'
!
!   Same as version ='SPH3DT-PTMAS-DEC+ACC-SR11000-06JAN2006', but
!     fixed a bug with ifsvi=6 option in forcei_P.f for decretion disk
!     +accretion disk simulations and added an Shakura-Sunyaev viscosity
!     parameter and SPH artificial viscosity parameter alpha_sph for
!     polytropic disks. It also includes boundary types 94 (colliding
!     stellar winds) and 99 (accretion disk with mass injection at the
!     outer boundary.
!
!   Same as version ='SPH3DT-PTMAS-GRAPE-O4-1.0-MRB-17-04-98'
!      but includes boundary types 92 and 93 and modified forcei(_P).f,
!      in which the artificial viscosity parameter alpha is variable
!      in space and time (beta=0) to emulates a contant Shakura-Suayev
!      viscosity parameter. This version is tuned for HITACHI SR11000
!      and uses IBM routine DSORTX instead of indexx in mtree_P.f.
!
!   Same as version ='SPH3DT-PTMAS-GRAPE-3.0-MRB-20-02-97' (sph3DTSP_GRAPE3_O4)
!      but includes boundary types 90 and 91 and new grape_main_split.f
!      from sph3DTSP_GRAPE3.
!      Similar to sph3DTSP_GRAPE3 but includes variable type of
!      Kernel (3rd and 4th order kernels) from sph3DTSP_GRAPE3_O4.
!      ALSO, can be compiled with either single or double precision.
!
!   Similar to version 'SPH3DT-PTMAS-GRAPE-1.0-MRB-27-04-96'
!
!   Same as version 'SPH3D-TIMESTEPS-PTMAS-5.03-MRB-01-06-95' (infall8)
!      but with TREE/GRAPE switchable computation.  Similar to
!      version 'SPH3D-TIMESTEPS-PTMAS-5.01-MRB-01-02-95'
!
!   Same as version SPH3D-TIMESTEPS-PTMAS-4.01-MRB-30-01-94,
!     but tidied up - all unused stuff thrown away (old boundaries,
!     excessive memory use etc).
!
!   Same as version SPH3D-TIMESTEPS-PTMAS-3.01-MRB-16-05-94,
!     with boundaries as used by Bate,Bonnell,Price 1995
!     but compiled under FORTRAN 90.
!
      nproc  = 1
      myrank = 0

!#ifdef SR16K
!      CALL XCLOCK(dummytime,7)
!#endif

!
!--Set debug and trace indicator
!
      idebug = 'off'
!!      idebug = 'toten'
!!      idebug = 'setpart'
      itrace = 'off'
!      itrace = 'all'
!
!--Floating point number error checking (DCR C routine)
!
!      CALL floating
!
!--Read main main option for run
!
      CALL mainop
!
!--Initialize physical, mathematical and astronomical constants
!
      CALL constan
!
!--Define code's units
!
!!      CALL unit
!
!--Execute main option
!
!  1) define new initial conditions
!
      IF (job(1:7).EQ.'initial') CALL newrun
!
!  2) transfer dumps to another file
!
!      IF (job(1:8).EQ.'transfer') CALL transfd
!
!  3) integrate the system
!
      IF (job(1:9).EQ.'evolution') CALL evol
!
!  4) reduce output files
!
      IF (job(1:6).EQ.'reduce') CALL reduce
!
!  5) extract an output file
!
      IF (job(1:7).EQ.'extract') CALL extract

      CALL quit

      END PROGRAM sph
